# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# aeon-radio-drama — environment variables
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy to `.env` and fill in your values. The 4 scripts (radio_drama.py,
# music_maker.py, music_mastering.py, sfx_maker.py) all read os.environ.
#
# Quick start:
#   cp .env.example .env && $EDITOR .env && ./setup.sh
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════


# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. ComfyUI server  (REQUIRED)
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# HTTP endpoint of your ComfyUI server. The pipeline never spawns ComfyUI;
# it only sends workflow JSONs and polls for results.
#
# ─── LOCAL MODE — ComfyUI on this machine ───────────────────────────────
#   COMFYUI_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8188
#
# ─── REMOTE MODE — ComfyUI on a different machine ───────────────────────
#   Option A (direct HTTP):
#     COMFYUI_URL=http://192.168.x.x:8188
#     # ComfyUI must be started with --listen 0.0.0.0 and firewall opens 8188
#
#   Option B (SSH tunnel — preferred):
#     # ssh -L 8188:127.0.0.1:8188 user@gpu-host  (in a separate terminal)
#     COMFYUI_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8188
#
COMFYUI_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8188


# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 2. ComfyUI install root  (REQUIRED for radio_drama.py)
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Unlike aeon-music-maker, the radio_drama.py orchestrator NEEDS this set
# because it builds a project layout (output/radio/<project>/audio/...)
# and reads/writes SFX library files at ${COMFYUI_ROOT}/input/sfx/.
#
# ─── LOCAL MODE: ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   Set this to the directory containing your ComfyUI install:
#     Linux/macOS:  COMFYUI_ROOT=/home/yourname/ComfyUI
#     Windows:      COMFYUI_ROOT=C:/Users/yourname/Documents/ComfyUI
#
# ─── REMOTE MODE: ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   Two sub-cases:
#
#   B1 — Run radio_drama.py LOCALLY against remote ComfyUI HTTP:
#     Set COMFYUI_ROOT to a LOCAL path where you'll stage SFX/script files.
#     The pipeline will write project files locally, but the model output
#     comes back via the ComfyUI HTTP API.
#     (NOTE: not all stages support this — file-based stages like manual
#     SFX library lookup expect local files. Best for fresh SFX gen.)
#
#   B2 — Run radio_drama.py ON the REMOTE machine (via SSH):
#     Set COMFYUI_ROOT to the remote machine's ComfyUI path.
#     SSH-invoke the CLI: ssh user@host 'cd repo && python scripts/...'
#     Best when SFX library is already populated on the remote box.
#
COMFYUI_ROOT=


# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 3. Output directory  (OPTIONAL)
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Where the pipeline puts output/radio/<project>/ trees. Defaults to
# ${COMFYUI_ROOT}/output if unset.
#
# OUTPUT_DIR=./output


# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 4. Binary paths  (OPTIONAL — uses PATH lookup)
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# FFMPEG=/usr/local/bin/ffmpeg
# FFPROBE=/usr/local/bin/ffprobe


# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 5. ACE Step variant default  (OPTIONAL)
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Default music quality. Choices: xl_base / xl_sft / xl_base_sft / xl_turbo / base_turbo.
# Per-cue 'variant' field in script.json always overrides.
#
# ACE_DEFAULT_VARIANT=xl_base


# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 6. SSH config  (OPTIONAL — only if you want to drive remote runs from helper scripts)
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# These are reference variables for documentation only; the Python CLI
# doesn't read them directly. They're used in shell snippets in AGENTS.md
# / SKILL.md / setup.sh as templates for users running radio_drama.py
# remotely via SSH.
#
# SSH_USER=
# SSH_HOST=


# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 7. HuggingFace token  (OPTIONAL — for gated model auto-download)
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Required only if you want `setup.sh` to fetch gated models (some MMAudio
# / Qwen3-TTS variants). Get a free token at:
#   https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens
# Choose "Read" access. Token starts with "hf_...".
#
# Most users won't need this — install models via ComfyUI Manager UI instead.
#
# HF_TOKEN=hf_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
